Link Bookman v. The State. No. 22334. Delivered December 16, 1942.

*165The opinion states the case.

Earl Shelton, of Austin, for appellant. Spurgeon E. Bell, State’s Attorney, of Austin, for the State. HAWKINS, Presiding Judge.

Conviction is for selling and possessing for the purpose of sale whisky without a license; punishment thirty days in jail.

No statement of facts is brought forward. We discover no question presented for review.

The judgment is affirmed.
